value.value: A classification of clinical observation data.

label.value: Clinical Observations Data Collection Date Time

value.value: The date and time of clinical observation data collection.
The study day that a clinical observation is made.

A synthetic complex of carboxymethylcellulose, polyinosinic-polycytidylic acid, and poly-L-lysine double-stranded RNA. Poly ICLC may stimulate the release of cytotoxic cytokines and, by inducing interferon-gamma production, may increase the tumoricidal activities of various immunohematopoietic cells. (NCI04)
The interval between two clinical observation reference time points.
A person who determines the significance of a clinical observation assessment.

label.value: Exclude Clinical Observation Data From Statistics Indicator

value.value: Specifies whether the clinical observation result values should be excluded from the statistical analysis.
A character or string that represents a clinical observation findings group.
The site in or on the body at which the clinical observation is made.
The outcome of the clinical observation as originally received or collected.

label.value: Clinical Observation Reason For Exclusion From Statistics

value.value: A rationale for excluding a particular data point or subject from the clinical observation statistical analysis.
The explanation given as to why a clinical observation was not made.

label.value: Clinical Observations Date Time of Reference Timepoint

value.value: The date and time of a specific reference point for the clinical observation.
An identifier that describes the relative position of clinical observation data within a series.
The degree of something undesirable as determined by clinical observations.
One or more sponsor defined characters used to identify, name, or characterize the clinical observation.
A term used to describe the state or condition of the completeness of the clinical observation data.

label.value: Clinical Observations Character Result in Standard Format

value.value: The standard character or string for representation and reporting of clinical observations data.
A character or string that represents the long name of the clinical observation assessment.
A character or string that represents the short code name of the clinical observation assessment.

label.value: Clinical Observations Planned Time Point Name

value.value: The literal identifier of a planned point in time for a clinical observation.

label.value: Clinical Observations Planned Time Point Number

value.value: The numerical identifier of a clinical observation point in time.
The point in time that acts as a fixed reference point to a clinical observation.
The study day that the comment pertains.
The level of awareness of an organism during an electrocardiogram assessment.

label.value: ECG Test Results End Date Time

value.value: The date and time an electrocardiogram assessment has concluded.
The final day of the electrocardiographic test.
The period of time during which an electrocardiogram was performed.

value.value: Specifies whether the ECG result values should be excluded from the statistical analysis.

label.value: ECG Reason For Exclusion From Statistics

value.value: A rationale for excluding a particular data point or subject from the ECG test results statistical analysis.
The technique used to administer the exposure treatment.

value.value: The final day of the food and water consumption assessment.
